    <has_dmc>Yes</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to investigate the effects of intraoperative P6 acupuncture plus
      standard therapy on postoperative nausea and vomiting in pediatric patients undergoing
      tonsillectomy with or without adenoidectomy. 200 children will be randomly assigned to either
      the treatment or the control group.

        1. Treatment Group: Standard anti-emetic therapy plus bilateral P6 acupuncture after the
           induction of anesthesia

        2. Control Group: Standard anti-emetic therapy only

      This study will monitor nausea, retching, and vomiting events both directly after the surgery
      as well as the next day via a follow-up phone call to the parents of the study participant.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
